description: First Lady Julia Grant is delivered to the mysterious Mr. Delkes. Lucita and Grant find a Tracker to help on their search for the outlaws. Colonel Marsh arrives to Harrisburg in search of the missing President. Meanwhile, Lucita and Grant encounter serious resistance.

The second issue of CELEBRATION takes on a slightly scarier theme, kicking off with the swingingest Monster Heroes of the high camp 60s facing off in "Frankenstein V Dracula '66." Then back to the 1950s for The Purple Claw as a TV Host declares "A Ghost Must Die!" And finally, Mazie Dean, the Hi-School Queen, learns just how frightening Homecoming Week can be.

Battle 8

An old friend from Dae's past comes to the Campbell's mansion to settle an old grudge. During the fight, Dae wonders if maybe he does deserve to die for his crimes.
name: Battle 8

description: Edge of Extinction Issue #3 begins with an ancient discovery. The Wolf and his organizations mission begin to come to light, as Jimbo and his crew make an even bigger find on the Moon.

Rehema makes her last stand to protect her son, Kwasi, from the stalking Witch Doctor and his harvester, Majuto, as these men hunting Kwasi for his white flesh launch an all-out siege on the village where Rehema took refuge. Will the help of the villagers and a little magical art of her own be enough to save her son?
Evil Strikes back.

The oversized, action packed, pants filled conclusion! Chet vs The Moon!

PLUS! An Operation Pajama Pants back-up adventure, because you could always use more pants!

Chapter Two

As the world tears itself apart and the plague continues to spread, one man tries to hold his family together.
name: Chapter Two

description:
Like Rubber and Glue

This is it, gang! Action, adventure, the beginning of a plot and actual stuff happening!
name: Like Rubber and Glue

description:
The Starting Line

Welcome to The Showdown! Revel in flames and fury as the racers take their place at the starting line. The race is about to begin!
name: The Starting Line

description:
When It Almost Happened

The Rats continue their plans unfazed by the commotion the Ravenwood cousins are causing. But something more is up their sleeves, something beyond just retrieving the Seal of Iberion. Meanwhile, Klea uncovers some interesting facts about the Earl Hadge that will prove dangerous for Prince Christian. And Ravenwood and Pandora's lives take an unexpected turn when she suddenly finds herself... a mother?
name: When It Almost Happened

description:
Summer: Chapter 3

Chapter 3 develops the further adventures of Teach English in Japan is a collaborative webcomic by Jeff Ellis and Jonathon Dalton. The story is based on Jeff and Jonathon's experiences teaching English in a foreign country. Jeff taught in the city of Kofu, Japan for two and a half years. Jonathon taught in Myauli and Taoyuan, Taiwan for a year and a half. They work collaboratively on the scripts, and Jeff creates the finished art.

It is their hope that this comic will give an accurate depiction of the trials and tribulations of living and working in a different culture. This story takes place in the year 2004 and is set to cover one year of life abroad for James K and James F.
name: Summer: Chapter 3

description: Earth was quarantined fifty years ago. Since then, long-running political and cultural clashes between Mars and Venus have intensified. Talk of revolution permeates the ether. Private Sam Reegan must make a choice. Either follow orders and squelch the Venusian resistance... or take up arms against Martian hypocrisy. Humanity is on the threshold of interplanetary war!

Serve Faceless Part Two

After fighting their way to safety, Harry Vild and Maari Matthews, think they are safe. But Bob, Vild's business partner, isn't happy about Maari tricking them. And the Queen of Faceless has not given up trying to capture Matthews! In fact the queen usurps Maari's mind, revealing the truth about the past.
name: Serve Faceless Part Two

description: 500 Portraits collects for the first time over two decades of portrait work by the beloved and award-winning creator of Drinky Crows Maakies, Sock Monkey and Billy Hazelnuts. Tony Millionaires gorgeous fountain pen illustrations, which mingle naturalistic detail with strong doses of the fanciful and grotesque, include the famous (Bob Dylan), the infamous (Abu Ghraib soldier/model Lynndie England), the fictional (Yoda), the animal kingdom (a cockroach), and everything in between. Literary figures (Hemingway), literary characters (Don Quixote and Sancho Panza), Hollywood legends (Steven Spielberg), comics icons (Herg) and historical figures (Hitler) also figure prominently.
name: HC

description:
Into The Belly of the Beast

In a land where chaos is embraced and war is the ultimate desire, order must be enforced. Enter the Battlecats. The most seasoned warriors in the land, fearless, determined, devout. This elite group travels the realm of Valderia fulfilling the king's mandates and displaying heroism worthy of the god they worship.

The Battlecats are about to embark on their most perilous quest yet: the hunt for the legendary Dire Beast. They will face the evils that plague LaMarque, Valderia's most haunted region, all while unraveling the origins of a holy war. The quest has begun...
name: Into The Belly of the Beast

description:
BEARS HAVE DECLARED WAR ON ALL HUMANS

From Axe Cop creator, Ethan Nicolle. This is the first volume collection of the web comic series Bearmageddon.

When Wow Mart employee, Joel Morley and his slacker friends ditch society to live in the forest, they discover a mass exodus of bears heading back to civilization to declare war on mankind. They enlist the help of a half-feral mountain man named Dickinson killdeer to aid them in returning to the city to find their families. But With bears mutating, growing tentacles and invading in massive numbers, it looks like the end of civilization as we know it.
name: Vol. 1

description: Beyond Doomsday is the new Illustrated comic book of fantasy, horror ans Science Fiction. This issue features five twisted tales of post armageddon terror. "The Transaction" (by frank Forte and Silvester Song) takes us on a dirty deal gone bad in the darkest regions of space. "Battlefield X" (by Frank Forte) brings us on the front lines of a bio-chemical war. "Mutation"(by Frank Forte and J.C. Wong) delivers a tale os post-nuke mutations and sexual deviancy which can only have disastrous results. Other tales incliude "Incident at Alpha Proxima" and "Short Circuit".
It's all ten issues of CAAATS! complied into one easy to read volume! Neat!

Chapter 1: The Fall

The saga begins as three unlikely heroes, Neriah, Christian and a strange alien named Kla'Tuu, embark on a dangerous journey to unearth the truth behind the disappearance of Neriah's only son, Avion. Monsterous beasts, ancient extraterrestrials and a mysteriously evil figure lurk in the darkness, setting out to destroy the team at every turn!
name: Chapter 1: The Fall

description:
In the distant future, the general population has become preoccupied with advanced technology and absurd entertainment. Too complacent to notice a world government run rampant with authority.

After a disastrous incident, a transport security agent goes off the books to investigate a strange occurrence at a local political convention. With the help of his eccentric confidential informant, they must uncover what the commercialized oligarchic government has been keeping a secret.

From The Ashes is a dark fantasy tale about a realm on the brink of extinction. The survivors of a magical armageddon attempt to piece their world together and find a way to turn back the tide of evil. Desperate times make for unlikely alliances as a group of heroes fight a losing battle against a Necromancer of unimaginable power.

They Took the World. And All We Have is Ourselves.

Sera loses her home, but may have found a new one. The Armless makes his first public appearance in what seems like ages.
A collection of short horror stories.

What Goes Around...

Jak McMannis is not a good guy. He stabs his partner in the back to take the fall while he steals money from the armored truck that they worked on. Later he finds that the evil he has done has come back to bite him, literally.
name: What Goes Around...

description:
Wyrmwood Secondary School has had the same grad prank for the past 50 years. This year Amber (a werewolf), Tiffany (a vampire), and Steph (a reptile) have set out to change that. The problem is, the school is cursed. And the end of school (forever) isn't going to go as planned.

Last Night at Wyrmwood High ran online from September 2014 - May 2015. It was published as an 84 page full colour graphic novel by Cloudscape Comics in 2016.
How does Casey cope with being the daughter of a man who left his family to become the world's only superhero.

Smoke in the Valley

A greedy bug lord wants to get his hands on the gold beneath a little town. But the villagers won't give up without a fight. Welcome to... Locust Valley!!
name: Smoke in the Valley

description:
Get the Midas Touch

Penny, a bossy, bookworm and her unpredictable little brother, Bobby, discover an incredible secret: Their mom's boss has been using a time machine to steel mythological artifacts. So they take action. With the evil boss on their tail, they race through time and myth to return every artifact to its rightful owner. First stop- King Midas.
name: Get the Midas Touch

description:
Neophytes

The team's debut is interrupted when they are attacked by another superhuman.
name: Neophytes

description:
Fathers and daughters don't always get along. But what better way to rekindle a strained relationship than to take a road trip across the entire country?

That's exactly what Lorne and Beth Zonkowski agree to do: drive from their home in central New Jersey to fabulous Las Vegas, Nevada--all to see Sir Tom Jones play a one-night-only show on the strip. But along with their suitcases, they've packed a trunkload of emotional baggage that only fourteen straight days in a car can unlock.

Will Beth and Lorne find happiness on the highway? Will their relationship survive 2,593 miles in a Golf GTI? And, most importantly, will they make it to Vegas in time to catch the show?

This volume collects the first 4 issues of Stargirl, the space adventure story of Lasha Trinity and her canine companion, Rover.

The story is set in the future after the Earth is no longer habitable and the human race lives in a ring-shaped space station that orbits the Earth.

Stargirl tells the story of Lasha Trinity and her dog, Rover, and the adventures they get into after the Earth ring-station is destroyed and the human race is plunged into a war with an alien race.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Valley of the Silk Sky: The Long Run Part 1

Being legally dead is causing Razi some problems, and xer only chance of escape from bureaucratic limbo will involve a dangerous trek through wolfcat territory.

Meanwhile, Halvanylila is supposed to be learning to hunt and fight, but it's hard to concentrate when there are fascinating plants to be scienced at.

Now they're both lost in the middle of nowhere, and they'll need each other's help and unique expertise to find their way out.

One problem: those wolfcats. Oh, wait, and a troupe of bandits? Two problems. But hey, as long as nothing else goes wrong ...
name: The Long Run Part 1

description: "Alienation, Incarceration, and Inebriation in the new American Rome." The collected 1997-2007 comics of Ken Dahl in this graphic novel anthology! Includes stories of airport security, the demeaning experience of being arrested, having to sell off his earthly possessions at a yard sale to pay the slumlord, the creative process of trying to write comics about "important" subjects, and much more. Additionally, we are treated to helpful guides to putting bananas in your cereal, peeing in the shower, and swinging at night. 2006 Ignatz Winner! 2007 Center for Cartoon Studies Resident! Winner of 2008 Expozine Alternative Press Award's "Best English Comic"!
Anna Cordero travels through space to Typhon, the man-made second moon of Earth. There she tours rolith Dynamics and learns about her ominous new assignment there.

After the startling conclusions to Wicker #0, Red Bear is left with few options, as lives hang in the balance, he returns to Andover to find the one man who may know what to do. Meanwhile panic and paranoia spread in Andover as the clergy prepares his own solutions as well . Tensions rise as time runs out in Wicker #1!

The Deconstruction Of Air Raid Robertson

Issue four contains three more adventures from comicdom's favorite quixotic aviator...

"SIngles Going Steady" - Air Raid Robertson and Ridley unwind at a local watering hole after completing yet another case. However, their reverie is interrupted by the fiendish needs of a classical riddle monster.

"Orange Blossom Special" - Ridley is tasked with solving a locked-room mystery on a speeding train. His usual partner is on stakeout, so Ridley's forced to endure the company of a guy who claims to be someone named Captain Marvel.

"The Family Clone" - The blood of an extradimensional urchin has the potential to be either a world-changing panacea or a source for horrific bio-weapons. Air Raid Robertson and Ridley are ordered to protect the boy until he can be sent home, but a shifty pharmaceutical company is desperate to acquire the boy; they're even willing to use evil clones to do it.
name: SIngles Going Steady; Orange Blossom Special; The Family Clone

description:
The Hunt for The Dire Beast

The Battelcats need to make their way through La Marque and fulfill their King's order- kill the evil Dire Beast that has haunted Stormholt for decades. But defeating the dangers of La Marque is easier said than done; they must overcome the most dreadful terrain in Stormholt and fight through the ancient deadly creatures that plague this region.

With Valadar the general of the evil Darkat army closely moving in, the Battlecats find themselves in a race to finish their mission and rush back to Stormholt to protect their King even if it means dying in the process.
name: The Hunt For The Dire Beast

description: Cangaceiros were "social bandits" in some regions of Brazil in the late 19th and early 20th century. They were nomads roaming the region in search of what they considered justice. They fought against land owners and government soldiers. To some people they were heroes, to others were bandits. Officially, the cangaceiros are extinct. But they are not extincts, damn it! There still is the funny Carrapicho, the last of the cangaceiros.
name: Vol. 2

description: The sinister Steel Shrike is on the rampage, and his targets are the people who work for Flare! With their glittering goddess of the light torn away to help the LEAGUE OF CHAMPIONS deal with a menace that threatens the survival of the entire planet, how in the world can her household staff possibly hope to protect themselves against the wrath of a vengeance-crazed killer? "The Revenge of the Steel Shrike," is an all-new Flare adventure by Lou Mougin and Dell Barras. Also in this issue, secrets of the origin of Flare are revealed in the classic tale, "Children of Wonder," by Dennis Mallonee, Keith Tucker, and Mark Beachum. Cover by Mark Beachum.
name: The Flare Crew: Home Defense 101; Children of Wonder
